ystem helps determine whether it undervalues its exchange rate and experiences explosive economic growth or if it overvalues its exchange rate and sees its economy stagnate as a result.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aForeign exchange ratesxPolitical aspectsxChina. 0aForeign exchange ratesxPolitical aspectsxDeveloping countriesxChinaxDeveloping countries. 0aForeign exchange ratesxPolitical aspectszChina. 0aForeign exchange ratesxPolitical aspectszDeveloping countries. 4aGeneral Economics. 4aPolitical Science & Political History.  aEconomic development, power of the dollar, international political conflict, international economic conflict, government economic policies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060674440uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978080145425740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780801454257423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780801454257/original  a978-3-11-060674-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles